translated: Östberg, Einar Wilhelm Otto, hospital physician, Växjö, born on May 14, 1899 in Lands-kr. to bank clerk Otto Emil Ö. and Hilda Elisabeth Grönwall. Married on March 31 to Monica Löwegren. Children: Görel Monica Anna Elisabeth, born in 1932, Per-Otto Ivar, born in 1934, Björn Otto Michaél, born in 1938, Clas Otto, born in 1943. Completed high school in Malmö in 1917, obtained a Bachelor of Medicine degree in 1921, became a licensed physician in 1926 and received a Doctor of Medicine degree in 1931 from Lund University. Worked as an assistant at the Anatomy Institute in Lund from 1920-1921, assistant there in 1924, became a physician, assistant, and deputy physician in the radiology department from 1925-1927, assistant and deputy physician in the medical clinic in Lund from 1928-1932, acting clinical laboratory director at Lund University from 1932-1933, taught clinical diagnostics in 1932 and led the course in general medical engineering in the same year, held various teaching positions at the medical clinic in Lund from 1930-1932, became a lecturer in practical medicine at Lund University from 1934-1938, clinical laboratory director and assistant lecturer in medicine from 1936-1938, chief physician at RamBsa from 1936-1938, and hospital physician at the medical department of Växjö hospital since 1939. Published papers and dissertations in physiology, chemistry, and internal medicine.
